—ظTarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/overlay_hide.mdظ@82a63e8930930bd1f6a4a7a73c6d20aea1e565397c5f92b1c3f0af0d210ca17e³title: overlay hide‘¨Examplesع¸Keep a custom command after hiding the overlay.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> module spam { export def foo [] { "foo" } }
    overlay use spam
    def bar [] { "bar" }
    overlay hide spam --keep-custom
    bar



```
Hide an overlay created from a file.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'export alias f = "foo"' | save spam.nu
    overlay use spam.nu
    overlay hide spam


```
Hide the last activated overlay.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> module spam { export-env { $env.FOO = "foo" } }
    overlay use spam
    overlay hide


```
Keep the current working directory when removing an overlay.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> overlay new spam
    cd some-dir
    overlay hide --keep-env [ PWD ] spam


```
’گگعëTitle: title: overlay hide
Path: Examples
Content:
Keep a custom command after hiding the overlay.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> module spam { export def foo [] { "foo" } }
    overlay use spam
    def bar [] { "bar" }
    overlay hide spam --keep-custom
    bar



```
Hide an overlay created from a file.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'export alias f = "foo"' | save spam.nu
    overlay use spam.nu
    overlay hide spam


```
Hide the last activated overlay.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> module spam { export-env { $env.FOO = "foo" } }
    overlay use spam
    overlay hide


```
Keep the current working directory when removing an overlay.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> overlay new spam
    cd some-dir
    overlay hide --keep-env [ PWD ] spam


```
